I"#<p>Founded as the world’s first twelve-step addiction recovery program in the 1930s, Alcohols Anonymous is a volunteer-led group practicing steps towards recovery as described in the organization’s <em>Big Book</em><sup id="fnref:1" role="doc-noteref"><a href="#fn:1" class="footnote" rel="footnote">1</a></sup>.</p>

<h3 id="rough-notes">Rough notes</h3>
<p>I’ve had conversations with <span title="This note is not for public consumption (yet)" class="invalid-link">  <span class="invalid-link-brackets"></span>  Caroline Jeffra  <span class="invalid-link-brackets"></span></span>, and I’ve heard podcast episodes about the dangers of this program and the AA culture. I should find exact sources to add to this note.</p>

